%F A000217 G.f.: x/(1-x)^3. - _Simon Plouffe_ in his 1992 dissertation
%F A000217 E.g.f.: exp(x)*(x+x^2/2).
%F A000217 a(n) = a(-1-n).
%F A000217 a(n) + a(n-1)*a(n+1) = a(n)^2. - _Terrel Trotter, Jr._, Apr 08 2002
%F A000217 a(n) = (-1)^n*Sum_{k=1..n} (-1)^k*k^2. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 29 2002
%F A000217 a(n+1) = ((n+2)/n)*a(n), Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n) = 2. - _Jon Perry_, Jul 13 2003
%F A000217 For n > 0, a(n) = A001109(n) - Sum_{k=0..n-1} (2*k+1)*A001652(n-1-k); e.g., 10 = 204 - (1*119 + 3*20 + 5*3 + 7*0). - _Charlie Marion_, Jul 18 2003
%F A000217 With interpolated zeros, this is n*(n+2)*(1+(-1)^n)/16. - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 19 2003
%F A000217 a(n+1) is the determinant of the n X n symmetric Pascal matrix M_(i, j) = binomial(i+j+1, i). - _Benoit Cloitre_, Aug 19 2003
%F A000217 a(n) = ((n+1)^3 - n^3 - 1)/6. - Xavier Acloque, Oct 24 2003
%F A000217 a(n) = a(n-1) + (1 + sqrt(1 + 8*a(n-1)))/2. This recursive relation is inverted when taking the negative branch of the square root, i.e., a(n) is transformed into a(n-1) rather than a(n+1). - _Carl R. White_, Nov 04 2003
%F A000217 a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} phi(k)*floor(n/k) = Sum_{k=1..n} A000010(k)*A010766(n, k) (R. Dedekind). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Feb 05 2004
%F A000217 a(n) + a(n+1) = (n+1)^2. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Feb 19 2004
%F A000217 a(n) = a(n-2) + 2*n - 1. - _Paul Barry_, Jul 17 2004
%F A000217 a(n) = sqrt(Sum_{i=1..n} Sum_{j=1..n} (i*j)) = sqrt(A000537(n)). - _Alexander Adamchuk_, Oct 24 2004
%F A000217 a(n) = sqrt(sqrt(Sum_{i=1..n} Sum_{j=1..n} (i*j)^3)) = (Sum_{i=1..n} Sum_{j=1..n} Sum_{k=1..n} (i*j*k)^3)^(1/6). - _Alexander Adamchuk_, Oct 26 2004
%F A000217 a(n) == 1 (mod n+2) if n is odd and a(n) == n/2+2 (mod n+2) if n is even. - _Jon Perry_, Dec 16 2004
%F A000217 a(0) = 0, a(1) = 1, a(n) = 2*a(n-1) - a(n-2) + 1. - _Miklos Kristof_, Mar 09 2005
%F A000217 a(n) = a(n-1) + n. - _Zak Seidov_, Mar 06 2005
%F A000217 a(n) = A108299(n+3,4) = -A108299(n+4,5). - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jun 01 2005
%F A000217 a(n) = A111808(n,2) for n > 1. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Aug 17 2005
%F A000217 a(n)*a(n+1) = A006011(n+1) = (n+1)^2*(n^2+2)/4 = 3*A002415(n+1) = 1/2*a(n^2+2*n). a(n-1)*a(n) = (1/2)*a(n^2-1). - _Alexander Adamchuk_, Apr 13 2006 [Corrected and edited by _Charlie Marion_, Nov 26 2010]
